---
Ânanda saw Sâriputra coming afar off, and he said to him： ‘Serene
and pure and radiant is your face, Brother Sâriputra! In what mood has
Sâriputra been today?’

‘I have been alone in Dhyâna, and to me came never the thought： I am
attaining it! I have got it! I have emerged from it!’
